JIRA only accept lower case usernames for login. That is a problem for us, because our users normaly have usernames with capital letters (in all other applications) and try to use these for JIRA too. 

So I made small modification to JIRA to convert the username to lower case at login:

*\includes\loginform.jsp*
org:
{noformat}<input class="text medium-field" id="login-form-username" name="os_username" type="text" value="<ww:property value="$os_username" />" />{noformat}

new:
{noformat}<input class="text medium-field" id="login-form-username" name="os_username" type="text" value="<ww:property value="$os_username" />" onchange="document.getElementById('login-form-username').value = document.getElementById('login-form-username').value.toLowerCase()" />{noformat} 


*login.xml* in atlassian-bundled-plugins.zip->jira-gadgets-plugin-4.2.1-b588.jar->gadgets
org:
{noformat}<input class="text medium-field" id="login-form-username" name="os_username" type="text" />{noformat}

new:
{noformat}<input class="text medium-field" id="login-form-username" name="os_username" type="text" onchange="document.getElementById('login-form-username').value = document.getElementById('login-form-username').value.toLowerCase()"/>{noformat}


There is also the file views/forgotlogindetails.jsp, but I don't know how to modify it. Maybe someone else can do it.

It would be great if this were in JIRA by default.

Best Regards,
Wilm

