Having to constantly update (non-Maven-built, non-Java) code to explicitly support the latest API versions seems painful.  It could help if we could take matters into our own hands programmatically via a method that lists the available API versions.  For example, performing a GET on:

http://example.com:8080/jira/rest/api/versions

could return
{noformat}
{
    "versions":[{
            "version": "1.0",
            "endpoint":"http://www.example.com/jira/rest/api/1.0/",
        },
        {
            "version": "2.0",
            "endpoint":"http://www.example.com/jira/rest/api/2.0/",
        },
        {   
            "version": "2.0.alpha1",
            "endpoint":"http://www.example.com/jira/rest/api/2.0.alpha1/",
        }
    ]
}
{noformat}

